content: I bought the app on Android and I can't record any videos..as the file won't save and disappears..help support is nonexistent Wasted my money..remote function also non existent
It doesn't record videos as advertised. The speed adjuster doesn't adjust and is glitchy. It's like the tortoise is the hare and the hare is the tortoise. I want a refund!

Does The Job But Has Bugs! I bought this app to help me build a online course. It does the job but I feel like for the price it definitely could be a little less buggy and I also think the design could be better. I am using an Android phone so that may be the reason it is a bit buggy. I noticed that when I copy a script from my word processor on my phone and then go back to the app it always freezes. I also think the speed and the font control should both be sliders at the bottom.

The Android version of this app is pretty useless. None of the remote capabilities of the other versions. Only reason I downloaded it was for the remote control option to go along with tablet version. Useless.

I have both iOS and Android, find something else on Android. The Android version is missing little things that the iOS version has. The speed of the script scrolling cannot be adjusted in the same manner as the iOS version and it glitches out 100% of the attempts to use it. There countdown feature is missing in the Android version. Creating a ticket with the "help" feature is aggravating and is unproductive. This is a great app in the iOS environment, and an poor port to Android.

This application is totally unusable. The speed difference between 20 and 19 is absolutely insane. At speed 20 I'm galloping away and tripping over my words. But at speed 19 I'm pausing for long gaps between sentences. Why on earth do you have so little granularity on the speed control??????? If you can't figure out how to implement better granularity why don't you support a remote control????? Why does the application hang everytime I try to make an edit on a file??? Refund requested.
Great app! Have used on my iPad and bought this the day it came out. Very smooth and easy to use.

The iOS version is five stars, absolutely. And this should be too, I see it allows use of remote control, which is great, and it also can film you as you read which is the best, BUT where is the feature that lets you squash all your text to the side of the screen near your camera, so you are looking right at the camera as you read? Is this key feature really missing? Or am I looking in the wrong place? Thanks!
replyContent: Hi Tamhas, thanks for your support! The feature you mention isn't missing as it's not really part of Teleprompter Premium. It's the defining feature of our other product Video Teleprompter on iOS. Teleprompter Premium is designed more as a professional studio or stage Teleprompter. Hopefully that clarifies in some way! ðŸ™‚
